    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-06-15T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-06-15T07:00:00-05:00" n="521"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d521">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">511.4A6/345: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-06-15T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 15, 1931—1 [<hi rend="italic">2?</hi>] p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 15—11:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. Made statement in Limitation Committee, June 13, to the effect that: <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>Quota plan in original form unacceptable to United States;</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>That if sufficiently changed to be satisfactory it would no longer be
                            in reality a quota plan, and that</item>
                        <label>(3)</label>
                        <item>Delegation considered principle of Franco-Japanese plan a more a basis
                            of [<hi rend="italic">acceptable</hi>] and practical basis for a
                            convention. I referred again to our hope that any convention concluded
                            would include provisions for the limitation of raw materials available
                            to factories and the consequent limitation of all derivatives.</item>
                        <label>(4)</label>
                        <item>The delegation placed before the Conference amendments to the first 16
                            articles of draft plan referred to in my telegram No. 13, <pb
                                facs="0774" n="660" xml:id="pg_660"/> June 10, 11 p.m. [<hi
                                rend="italic">a.m.</hi>], with explanatory statement. Copies of
                            speech, articles and explanation by open mail.<note n="99"
                                xml:id="d521fn99">Not printed.</note>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
